nh.alpha <- c('H','I')
cx <- list()
for (i in 1:length(nh.alpha)) {
  # read XPT file by year
  cx[[i]] <- list.files(pattern = paste0("*",nh.alpha[i],".XPT"))
}
index <- list()
index.vb <- list()
for (i in 1:length(nh.alpha)) {
  for (j in 1:length(cx[[1]])) {
    # read the database for the same year and store it in an inner list
    index.vb[[j]] <- data.frame(read.xport(cx[[i]][j]))
  }
  # store databases for different years in an outer list based on their respective years
  index[[i]] <- index.vb
}
names(index) <- nh.alpha 
for (i in 1:length(nh.alpha)) {
  names(index[[i]]) <- c('ALB_CR','ALQ','BMX','BPQ','DEMO','DIQ','EPHPP','GHB','GLU','OGTT','PHTHTE','SMQ')
}
name.h_i <- list()
for (i in 1:length(nh.alpha)) {
  # select chemical variables' name
  name.h_i[[i]] <- index[[i]]$PHTHTE %>% 
    select(-SEQN,-WTSB2YR) %>% names #-ends_with('LC'),
}

Data cleaning

raw <- as.data.frame(read.csv("chemicalmixtures.csv", header = TRUE))
raw <- raw %>% filter(!(is.na(LBXGH) & is.na(DIQ010) & is.na(DIQ050) & 
                          is.na(DIQ070) & is.na(LBXGLU) & is.na(LBXGLT))) %>% 
  mutate(
    weight.final = WTSB2YR/nrow(distinct(raw,SDDSRVYR)),
    ALQ151   = factor(case_when(ALQ151 == 1 ~ 'Yes',
                                ALQ151 == 2 ~ 'No'),
                      levels = c('No','Yes')),
    RIAGENDR = factor(case_when(RIAGENDR == 1 ~ 'Male',
                                RIAGENDR == 2 ~ 'Female'),
                      levels = c('Female','Male')),
    RIDRETH1 = factor(case_when(RIDRETH1 == 1 ~ 'MexicanAmerican',
                                RIDRETH1 == 2 ~ 'OtherHispanic',
                                RIDRETH1 == 3 ~ 'NonHispanicWhite',
                                RIDRETH1 == 4 ~ 'NonHispanicBlack',
                                RIDRETH1 == 5 ~ 'OtherRace'),
                      levels = c('MexicanAmerican','OtherHispanic',
                                 'NonHispanicWhite','NonHispanicBlack','OtherRace')),
    DMDEDUC2 = factor(case_when(DMDEDUC2 == 1 | DMDEDUC2 == 2 ~ 'LowerThanHighSchool',
                                DMDEDUC2 == 3 ~ 'HighSchool',
                                DMDEDUC2 == 4 ~ 'SomeCollegeOrAAdegree',
                                DMDEDUC2 == 5 ~ 'CollegeGraduate'),
                      levels = c('LowerThanHighSchool','HighSchool',
                                 'SomeCollegeOrAAdegree','CollegeGraduate')),
    BPQ020   = factor(case_when(BPQ020 == 1 ~ 'Yes',
                                BPQ020 == 2 ~ 'No'),
                      levels = c('No','Yes')),                    
    SMK      = factor(case_when(SMQ020 == 2 ~ 'NeverSmoker',
                                SMQ020 == 1 & SMQ040 == 3 ~ 'FormerSmoker',
                                SMQ020 == 1 & (SMQ040 == 2 | SMQ040 == 1) ~ 'CurrentSmoker'),
                      levels = c('NeverSmoker','FormerSmoker','CurrentSmoker')),
    T2D.cat  = factor(case_when(LBXGH  >= 6.5 ~ 'Yes',
                                DIQ010 == 1   ~ 'Yes',
                                LBXGLU >= 126 ~ 'Yes',
                                DIQ050 == 1   ~ 'Yes',
                                DIQ070 == 1   ~ 'Yes',
                                LBXGLT >= 200 ~ 'Yes',
                                TRUE          ~ 'No'),
                      levels = c('No','Yes'))# Identify diabetic patients.
  )

Spearman correlation between chemical metabolites

library(corrplot)
library(ggplot2)
library(ggpubr)
library(Hmisc)
library(psych)

Plot Figure S2A

Spearman correlation among phthalate metabolites

phthalate <- SE[,c(14:25)]
colnames(phthalate) <- c("MCNP","MCOP","MnBP","MEP","MEHP","MBzP","MCPP", "MEHHP",
                         "MEOHP","MiBP","MECPP","MHNCH"
)
cor_phthalate <- cor (phthalate, method="spearman")
testRes = cor.mtest(phthalate, method="spearman",conf.level = 0.95)
addcol <- colorRampPalette(c("red", "white", "blue"))
corrplot(cor_phthalate, method = "color", col = addcol(100), 
         tl.col = "black", tl.cex = 0.8, tl.srt = 45,tl.pos = "lt",
         p.mat = testRes$p, diag = T, type = 'upper',
         sig.level = c(0.001, 0.01, 0.05), pch.cex = 1.2,
         insig = 'label_sig', pch.col = 'grey20', order = 'AOE')
corrplot(cor_phthalate, method = "number", type = "lower",col = addcol(100), 
         tl.col = "n", tl.cex = 0.8, tl.pos = "n",order = 'AOE',
         add = T)

# remove outliers
outlierResult <- car::outlierTest(chemical.logi)
if (outlierResult$bonf.p[1] < 0.05) {
  exclusionRows   <- names(outlierResult[[1]])
  inclusionRows   <- !(rownames(mydata) %in% exclusionRows)
  mydata.logi.out <- mydata[inclusionRows,]
  logi.last       <- glm(formula = formula.chemicals, family  = binomial(link = "logit"), data = mydata.logi.out)
} else {logi.last <- chemical.logi;mydata.logi.out <- mydata}
# remove high leverage points
leverage.con <- names(which(hatvalues(logi.last) > 
                              3 * length(coefficients(logi.last))/length(fitted(logi.last))))
if (length(leverage.con) > 0) {
  exclusionRows   <- leverage.con
  inclusionRows   <- !(rownames(mydata.logi.out) %in% exclusionRows)
  mydata.logi.out <- mydata.logi.out[inclusionRows,]
  logi.last       <- glm(formula = formula.chemicals,family  = binomial(link = "logit"), data = mydata.logi.out)
}

# remove influential points
influential <- which(cooks.distance(logi.last) 
                     > 4/(nrow(mydata.logi.out)-length(logi.last$coefficients)-2))
if (length(influential) > 0){
  exclusionRows <- rownames(mydata.logi.out)[influential]
  inclusionRows <- !(rownames(mydata.logi.out) %in% exclusionRows)
  mydata.logi.out <- mydata.logi.out[inclusionRows,]
  logi.last <- glm(formula = formula.chemicals,family  = binomial(link = "logit"), data = mydata.logi.out)
}

cat("Number of removed samples:",dim(mydata)[1] - dim(mydata.logi.out)[1])
## Number of removed samples: 401
cat("Number of removed samples:",dim(mydata)[1] - dim(mydata.logi.out)[1])
## Number of removed samples: 401
# Number of removed samples: 401

# the independence of observations was performed by Durbin-Wastons test
library(performance)
performance::check_autocorrelation(logi.last)
## OK: Residuals appear to be independent and not autocorrelated (p = 0.160).
performance::check_model(logi.last,check=c('outliers'))

mydata.logi.out <- mydata.logi.out %>% mutate(
  prob = predict(logi.last,type = 'response'),
  logitP = log(prob/(1-prob))
)
reg.formula.logi.linear <- update(formula.chemicals, logitP ~ .)
logi.linear <- lm(formula = reg.formula.logi.linear, data = mydata.logi.out)
performance::check_model(logi.linear,check=c('linearity'))

# weighted median and IQR
library(Hmisc)
wtd.IQR <- function(x,weights){
  wtd.quantile(x,weights,probs=0.75) - wtd.quantile(x,weights,probs=0.25)
}
